OL,3,CConclave: How is a new Pope elected?
OL,5,FFor centuries, leaders of the Roman
OL,6,FCatholic Church have been chosen at
OL,7,Fthe Vatican in private gatherings
OL,8,Fknown as conclaves.
OL,10,FThe historic vote, which often happens
OL,11,Fbetween 15 to 20 days after the Pope's
OL,12,Fdeath, is shrouded in secrecy.
OL,14,FWho can be pope?
OL,16,FAny baptised Catholic can be elected
OL,17,Fpope, but since 1379 every pope has
OL,18,Fbeen selected from the College of
OL,19,FCardinals - the group who cast the
OL,20,Fvotes at the conclave.
