OL,3,CConclave: How is a new Pope elected?
OL,5,FThe cardinals are handed voting papers
OL,6,Fto write the name of the person they
OL,7,Fhave selected.
OL,9,FOne by one - in order of seniority -
OL,10,Fthey take it in turns to approach the
OL,11,Faltar where they leave it on a plate,
OL,12,Fpray, below the words "Eligo in Summun
OL,13,FPontificem" - Latin for "I elect as
OL,14,Fsupreme pontiff" - and then place it
OL,15,Fin an urn.
OL,17,FThe names are then counted and if a
OL,18,Fname has received two-thirds of the
OL,19,Fvotes, the pope has been elected.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
